    <content><![CDATA[<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt;">The Prime Ministerâs Literary Awards are Australiaâs richest literary prize. The awards highlight the depth and diversity of Australiaâs literary talent in prose, poetry, scholarship, imagination and illustration. </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt;">Â </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt;">They illustrate the continuing commitment of the Commonwealth Government to the promotion and celebration of the best in Australian writing, as well as ongoing support for the Australian publishing industry. </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt;">Â </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt;">When entries for the 2014 awards closed, there were more than 480 entrants across six categories â fiction, non-fiction, poetry, history, childrenâs and young adult. </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt;">Â </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;; font-size: 12pt;">We are pleased to announce that the judges for the 2014 Prime Ministerâs Literary Awards are:</span></p>
